  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, by reason of its excessive footprint, position and location would result in an obtrusive form of development which would fail to respect the character and appearance of the terraced buildings along Gloucester Drive. As such the proposed development is contrary to policies D3 (Optimising Site Capacity through the Design-led Approach) and D4 (Delivering good design) of the London Plan 2021, LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) and LP17 (Housing Design) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;Insufficient and inaccurate information regarding trees has been submitted with this application. The Local Planning Authority is therefore unable to fully assess the merits or otherwise of this proposal and its impact on existing trees which fails to comply with Policy LP51 (Tree Management and Landscaping) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to contribute towards the Carbon Offset Fund,&amp;nbsp; would fail to meet the London Objective of being a zero-carbon city by 2050, contrary to policies SI 2 (Minimising greenhouse gas emissions) of the London Plan (2021), policy&amp;nbsp; LP55 (Mitigating Climate Change) of Hackneyâs Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure car-free housing, would be likely to promote the use of non-sustainable modes of transport and contribute to air pollution and congestion in the surrounding area, contrary to policies T6 (Car Parking) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP45 (Parking and Car Free Development) of Hackneyâs Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, by reason of sub-standard layout to the proposed residential accommodation for Flat 1, would result in the provision of an unacceptable standard of residential accommodation. As such the proposed development is contrary to policy D6 (Housing Quality and Standards) of London Plan 2021 and policy LP17 (Housing Design) of the Local Plan 2033 and the guidance contained within the Mayor of London&#x27;s Housing SPG.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of the provision of genuinely affordable housing or a legal agreement to secure a contribution in lieu towards affordable housing fails to deliver the maximum reasonable amount of affordable housing and is therefore contrary to policy H4 (Delivering affordable housing) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP13 (Affordable housing) of Hackneyâs Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, by reason of its size, design and position, would result in harm to the amenity of the neighbouring residents to 5 Gloucester Drive in regard to being an overbearing development with an increased sense of enclosure, and increased overlooking to the detriment of these neighbouring residents amenity.&amp;nbsp; As such the proposed development is contrary to policies D3 (Optimising Site Capacity through the Design-led Approach) D6 (Housing Quality and Standards) of the London Plan 2021, and policy LP2 (Development and Amenity) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;"
  ],
